The Chapter Acts here printed for the first time include a great many institutions of canons, vicars, and others, which add several new names to those in the Fasti Riponienses in our second volume. Among these are no less than fourteen names of canons not previously known, viz.: John de Clifford, upon whose death in or before 1393 William de Cawood was admitted to the prebend of Thorp; F ranciscus presbyter Cardinalis tituli iiij0r coronatorum, admitted to the prebend of Monkton about 1411; John de Columba, who had held a prebend before c. 1233i Peter de Fikelden‚ who held a prebend that had been held by Will. de Orliens‚ c. 1228-1234; T. de G., concanonicus, 1306-1352; Adam de Melsenby, witness 1228 and c. 1235; Milo,

Besides these new names, we gather several new dates and particulars belonging to canons already known, and many hitherto unknown appoint- ments of vicars and other officers of the church.
